Creates a dot file of the following form:

digraph <name> {
s1 [shape=ellipse,color=black,label="D"];
s2 [shape=ellipse,color=black,label="B"];
s3 [shape=ellipse,color=black,label="C"];
s1 -> s2 [color="firebrick4",arrowhead=tee,label="2"];
s1 -> s3 [color="blue4",arrowhead=vee];
}

tee for repression
vee for activation

New -> Network

to open the editor

Add Node
Remove Node
Edit Node

Node has an id (must be unique) and name (goes in label field)

Add Connection
Remove Connection
Edit Connection

Connection select source label and sink label, type of influence 
(Repression "tee" or Activation "vee"), edge label "label".




